ED_Title: Interactive  dialogue on Harmony with Nature
ED_DecisionText:
On 13 April 2020, the General Assembly, on the proposal of its President (A/74/L.46),  recalling its resolution 74/224 of 19 December 2019, in which the President of the General Assembly had been requested to convene, at its seventy-fourth session, an interactive dialogue, to be held at the plenary meetings to be convened during the commemoration of International Mother Earth Day on 22 April 2020, and noting with concern the situation concerning the coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19), 

Decided to cancel the interactive dialogue on Harmony with Nature scheduled to be held during the seventy-fourth session of the General Assembly.
ED_Disclaimer: The final version of decisions adopted during the resumed part of the session will be contained in the official record of the GA (A/74/49 (Vol. III)) after editorial review.
